![image](https://github.com/zulip/zulip/assets/64723994/56c30f4e-7a9a-4765-a97e-cf1eb268e260)
', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 9, 12, 19, 35, 36, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Ddharmani3', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1326395312, 'comment_body': "Is the reasoning that `unread_mentions_counter` doesn't get those wildcard mentions, so `direct_message_with_mention_count` doesn't need them?", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 9, 14, 18, 55, 3, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'timabbott', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1327331367, 'comment_body': '@timabbott Here is an explanation, it is a little longðŸ˜…, hope I explained it clearly:

<details>
  <summary>Code</summary>

   ```javasript
    const is_unmuted_mention =
        message.type === "stream" &&
        message.mentioned &&
        !user_topics.is_topic_muted(message.stream_id, message.topic);

    if (is_unmuted_mention || message.mentioned_me_directly) {
        unread_mentions_counter.add(message.id);
        add_message_to_unread_mention_topics(message.id);
        if (!message.stream_id) {
            direct_message_with_mention_count.add(message.id);
        }
    }
   ```

</details>

In the `update_message_for_mention` function, `unread_mentions_counter` is increased if `is_unmuted_mention` is true or `message.mentioned_me_directly` is true and `direct_message_with_mention_count` is increased too but only if the message is a direct message.

so for `@user` and `@group` mentions in direct messages, `direct_message_with_mention_count` is increased as `message.mentioned_me_directly` is true for them. 

But for `@all` and `@everyone` mentions in direct messages, `direct_message_with_mention_count` is not increased as 
`message.mentioned_me_directly` is false and `is_unmuted_mention` is also false as `message.type != "stream"` in `is_unmuted_mention` calculation.

And you are correct that the reasoning is that `unread_mentions_counter` also doesn't get wildcard mentions, in fact, wildcard mentions in direct mentions are not counted as mentions at all, which is a bug I have also reported on [CZO](https://chat.zulip.org/#narrow/stream/6-frontend/topic/Wildcard.20mentions.20in.20direct.20messages/near/1641123).

But they are not considered as mentions only until the page reloads due to [this bug](https://chat.zulip.org/#narrow/stream/6-frontend/topic/Wildcard.20mentions.20in.20direct.20messages/near/1641123), but after reloading they are counted as mentions, as after reloading counting is done in the `initialize()` function of `unread.js`, which handles all the mentions correctly and also increases `direct_message_with_mention_count` correctly. That's why I commented that it handles all the cases correctly and the screenshot is also after page reloading.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 9, 15, 14, 0, 59, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Ddharmani3', 'type': 'User'}]
